### Cell Ranger on the scRNAseq ###
# Originally a Chromium Multiome must be downstream analyzed with Cell Ranger Arc, created specifically for the multiome chemistry.
# However, due to the type of sequencing the ATAC data is unanalyzable at this point, and the Cell Ranger ARC cannot process only the RNAseq data.
# Therefore, we used the normal Cell Ranger Count with an argument specifying the type of chemistry (ARC) and downprocessed only the RNAseq.

cd /scratch/mozturk/Pilot1/

nice -n 19 ~/cellranger-10.0.0/cellranger count \
  --id=GEX_only_SI_TT_C9 \
  --create-bam=true \
  --transcriptome=/mbshome/mozturk/refdata-gex-GRCh38-2020-A \
  --fastqs=/scratch/mozturk/Pilot1/scRNA_bcl2fastq_mm1/fastqs \
  --sample=SI_TT_C9 \
  --chemistry=ARC-v1 \
  --localcores=6 \
  --localmem=64
